reviews.text: Really nicely decorated that gives it some character in a really good location. Our room was tiny but maybe not for Hong Kong, and theres a lounge with free snacks and coffee/tea to relax and stretch out. The bathroom and shower were awesome and we had a really nice view. Take a cab to get there unless you know where you are going.

One of the best boutique hotels in town with unbeatable location and price quality value. The staff are all very friend and helpful. Rooms are a bit small but that’s just HK prime location. Hotel is contemporary Asian deco. They also have a handmade where to go about guide in Central, which beats any tour guide

2.5 ⭐Needs a lot of cleaning and updates. The location is great. Walking distance to everything.  The rugs, walls, hallways needs deep cleaning.  The bathroom is old school. Rooms are tiny.. I guess that's normal in HK island.

I stay at this hotel about once a month and  I always Ienjoy my stay here. Rooms are small, however by Hong Kong standards they are slightly larger. It's in an extremely convenient location. The staff at front desk & in the breakfast room are a delight.

Recently engineering, Tai & Joey, rescued my earring from the depth of plumbing.

Hotel rooms were good. Even great, better than was to be expected for the price. The service was excellent, laundry service was great. However, on weekends, the noise from nearby clubs could be very loud until 10 at night, so I would not recommend for families with young children that go to bed early.

reviews.text: Really cool place. Trending and modern. Urban culture. Variety. Nightlife. Bars and clubs. Beautiful people. Crazy dressed people. Everyone as he likes. I really enjoyed walking through this neighborhood and soaking up the energy. That gives impressions of which one can still feed for a long time. Very inspiring. Very recommendable.

7-11 is the landmark of Lan Kwai Fong
I saw mamy people just buy drinks there when they feel drunk a little bit just get in to the club for dance 💃🕺 tonight I get in to Graffiti club

🍷today is Saturday ladies entrance for free but man pay 100$ that 100$ will be the coupon for drink in side   only beer   choose only one drink (beer only) and they will take your coupon

They play old songs here (we will rock you,I love it,Rude.. ) i was stay there just only 20 minutes

you will have a great time if you like crowds and the night goers. you can pop into a bar or grab drinks from 7-11 and hang out in the street. be careful as the sun will be rising before you know it. 

unfortunately broke phone the night of so I lost my photos to share
Cool street lined up with bars. Not a fan of the men grabbing my friend and me to get us to go into their bars. Beware of false deals that they’ll say to get you to go inside.

Safe and fun. 
The cocktail here taste good and people do dance.

reviews.text:
좋은 위치(홍콩역에서 미드레벨에스칼레이터 타고 오면 많이 안 걸어도 됨) 친절한 직원 적당한 조식 
패밀리룸은 그 가격에 홍콩 안에서 경쟁상대 없음. 호텔닷컴 골드멤버면 late check out 과 웰컴기프트로 와인을 공짜로 받을 수 있음
가격대비 많이 아쉬움. 샤워만 가능한데 세면대 샤워실 모두 물이 잘 안 내려감. 직원들은 친절하지 않음. 다신 안 갈거임.
캐리어가 크고 무겁다면  우버로 호텔까지 이동하는게 낫습니다. 경사가 져서 힘들어요. 호텔 위치는 소호 돌아다니기는 좋아요. 방과 화장실 모두 좀 어둡고 칙칙합니다. 그냥 잠만 자고 샤워하실 정도의 용도입니다.
오리엔탈 컨셉이 맘에들어 예전부터 찜했었다가 방문! 낡은 느낌이 있지만 지저분한 느낌은 아님! 뷰도 좋고 서비스도 괜찮지만 방이 많이 좁은거 참고하시길

Really nicely decorated that gives it some character in a really good location. Our room was tiny but maybe not for Hong Kong, and theres a lounge with free snacks and coffee/tea to relax and stretch out. The bathroom and shower were awesome and we had a really nice view. Take a cab to get there unless you know where you are going.
